As I write this review, I'm sitting here eating these warm, succulent tea biscuits and I (immodestly) say, they're absolutely WONDERFUL ! ;-) I've made them a few times and this time I used half shortening and half butter, which seems to have worked out very well. Tips for GREAT biscuits that I've learned from better bakers than me include:
- Don't overmix or over-handle the dough. It should be craggy and rough, not smooth and stretchy like bread dough;
- Press your biscuit cutter straight up-and-down, don't twist it;
- Let the cut biscuits "rest" on the baking sheet for about 10 minutes before baking;
- Brush the top of each biscuit with milk before baking for a lovely golden finish. 
THANK YOU DEBBIE for this great recipe!!! It's as good as my grandmother's, and that's hard to beat.
